public class JSourceUnmarshallerBase

Base class for public unmarshallers. __TEST__ Most unmarshalble code fragments still untested for unmarshalling failure.

unmarshal

public JavaSource unmarshal(java.io.File pJavaSource,
                            java.util.List<java.lang.String> pErrorMessages)
                     throws JSourceUnmarshallerException
Unmarshals a complete Java source file.

Parameters:
pJavaSource - The Java source that should get unmarshalled.
pErrorMessages - If the parser reports one or more errors it depends on this argument what will happen. If this argument is null all the error messages will be written to System.err . Ohterwise the error messages will be added to the given list and each list entry will correspond to one error line as reported by the parser.
Returns:
A JSOM object of type JavaSource. If marshalling the file has been failed but no exception has been thrown null will be returned and it's very likely that there's at least one message within the message list passed to this method (if a list has been passed at all, of course).
Throws:
JSourceUnmarshallerException - if marshalling the Java file failed.

unmarshalExpression

public Expression unmarshalExpression(java.lang.String pExpression,
                                      java.util.List<java.lang.String> pErrorMessages)
                               throws JSourceUnmarshallerException
Unmarshals any kind of expressions stated as string.

Important note: The given string must represent a complete expression in a sematical point of view, i.e. an assignment statement, a 'new' expression, a method call and so on. Unmarshalling of a fraction of a complete expression may succeed but this is not guaranteed. For instance, unmarshalling just a primiary expression representing an array type declaration (something like anyType[] ) will always fail.

Parameters:
pExpression - The expression that should get unmarshalled.
pErrorMessages - If the parser reports one or more errors it depends on this argument what will happen. If this argument is null all the error messages will be written to System.err . Ohterwise the error messages will be added to the given list and each list entry will correspond to one error line as reported by the parser.
Returns:
A JSOM object of type Expression.
Throws:
JSourceUnmarshallerException - if marshalling the code fragment failed.

unmarshalGenericTypeArgumentList

public java.util.List<? extends GenericTypeArgument> unmarshalGenericTypeArgumentList(java.lang.String pGenericTypeArgumentList,
                                                                                      java.util.List<java.lang.String> pErrorMessages)
                                                                               throws JSourceUnmarshallerException
Unmarshals a generic type argument list stated as string.

Note that this method doesn't return an object representing a generic type argument list. Instead the generic type arguments will be resolved from the parsed generic type argument list and these resolved generic type arguments will be returned.

Parameters:
pGenericTypeArgumentList - The generic type argument list that should get unmarshalled. Note that this must be a complete generic type argument list including the angle brackets.
pErrorMessages - If the parser reports one or more errors it depends on this argument what will happen. If this argument is null all the error messages will be written to System.err . Ohterwise the error messages will be added to the given list and each list entry will correspond to one error line as reported by the parser.
Returns:
A list containing one or more JSOM objects of type GenericTypeArgument resolved from the given generic type argument list. If marshalling the code fragment has been failed but no exception has been thrown null will be returned and it's very likely that there's at least one message within the message list passed to this method (if a list has been passed at all, of course).
Throws:
JSourceUnmarshallerException - if marshalling the code fragment failed.
